value.value: 鼓室の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the small, air-filled, mucosa-lined cavity that is located in the petrous portion of the temporal bone and houses the auditory ossicles and intratympanic muscles (tensor tympani and stapedius) as well as the chorda tympani and the tympanic plexus of nerves; it is split into two parts: the tympanic cavity proper (the space directly internal to the tympanic membrane) and the epitympanic recess or attic (the space superior to the tympanic membrane)

value.value: 鼓室の欠如

absence of the small, air-filled, mucosa-lined cavity that is located in the petrous portion of the temporal bone and houses the auditory ossicles and intratympanic muscles (tensor tympani and stapedius) as well as the chorda tympani and the tympanic plexus of nerves
耳小骨筋の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of either of the two tiny striated muscles (tensor tympani and stapedius) located within the tympanic cavity; these muscles contract in response to loud noise, inhibiting the vibrations of the malleus, incus and stapes, and reducing the transmission of sound to the inner ear

value.value: アブミ骨筋の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the tiny striated muscle found in the pyramidal eminence on the posterior wall of the tympanic cavity, whose tendon inserts onto the neck of the stapes; like the tensor tympani, it helps to dampen loud sounds; it is innervated by a small branch from the facial nerve

value.value: アブミ骨筋の欠如
missing the tiny muscle normally found in the pyramidal eminence on the posterior wall of the tympanic cavity, whose tendon inserts onto the neck of the stapes
鼓膜張筋の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the tiny striated muscle that originates superior to the pharyngotympanic tube, the sphenoid, and the temporal bone and inserts into the handle of the malleus; it tenses the tympanic membrane and dampens the movements of the auditory ossicles to prevent ear damage from loud sounds; it is innervated by the trigeminal nerve

value.value: 耳嚢形態異常

any structural anomaly of the hollow bony structure on the ventral, posterior portion of the skull that encloses parts of the middle and inner ear; in most species, it is formed by the tympanic part of the temporal bone
耳骨胞の欠如

absence of the hollow bony structure normally found on the ventral, posterior portion of the skull that encloses parts of the middle and inner ear; in most species, it is formed by the tympanic part of the temporal bone
舌骨体の欠如
absence of the main curve of the hyoid bone from which the horns extend
眼角形態異常

any structural anomaly of either corner of the eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet; more specifically, the inner and outer canthi are, respectively, the medial and lateral ends/angles of the palpebral fissure
目頭の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the inner corner of the eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet, i.e. the medial end/angle of the palpebral fissure
目尻の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the outer corner of the eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet, i.e. the lateral end/angle of the palpebral fissure
内眼角距離の増加
increased distance between the inner corners (medial canthi) of the eyes where the eyelids meet; may be present without or with ocular hypertelorism (where interpupillary distance is increased)
目頭の距離の減少
decreased distance between the inner corners (medial canthi) of the eyes where the eyelids meet
上口唇の薄化
upper lips having a reduced amount of soft tissue
上口唇の肥厚
upper lips having an abundance and often an excess of soft tissue
下顎結合の欠如
absence of the fibrocartilagenous union of the two halves of the mandible (embryonic stages)
外眼筋の欠如
missing the striated muscles that are located within the orbit but are extrinsic and separate from the eyeball itself and control the movements of the eyeball and the superior eyelid
眼瞼筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of any of the muscles that attach to an eyelid
眼輪筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the ring-like (sphincter) facial muscle composed of skeletal muscle fibers and arranged in concentric bands around the upper and lower eyelids; its function is to close the eyelids, and to help in the passing and draining of tears through the punctum, canaliculi, and lacrimal sac, all parts of the tear drainage system
眼輪筋の欠如
absence of the ring-like (sphincter) facial muscle composed of skeletal muscle fibers and arranged in concentric bands around the upper and lower eyelids; its primary function is to close the eyelids
眼輪筋の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the orbicularis oculi muscle, typically resulting in decreased size

label.value: abnormal levator labii superioris muscle morphology

value.value: 上唇挙筋の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal levator labii superioris muscle morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the facial muscle that is shaped like a broad, flat sheet, the origin of which extends from the side of the nose to the zygomatic bone; its main function is to elevate the upper lip
上唇挙筋の欠如
missing the facial muscle that is shaped like a broad, flat sheet, the origin of which extends from the side of the nose to the zygomatic bone; its main function is to elevate the upper lip
頭皮の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the soft tissue envelope of the cranial vault that extends from the external occipital protuberance and superior nuchal lines to the supraorbital margins; it consists of 5 layers: the skin (and head hair), connective tissue, epicranial aponeurosis, loose areolar tissue, and pericranium; the first 3 layers are bound together as a single unit that can move along the loose areolar tissue over the pericranium, which is adherent to the calvaria

value.value: 口腔上皮の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the stratified squamous epithelium that forms part of the oral mucosa and lines the inner aspect of the oral cavity; depending on the mouth region, the epithelium may be non-keratinized or keratinized; non-keratinized squamous epithelium covers the soft palate, inner lips, inner cheeks, and the floor of the mouth, and ventral surface of the tongue; keratinized squamous epithelium is present in the attached gingiva and hard palate as well as areas of the dorsal surface of the tongue
鼻びれ形態異常

any structural anomaly of the transient epithelial seam that develops by fusion between the epithelial linings of the medial and lateral nasal swellings; shortly after its formation the nasal fin regresses and is replaced by mesenchyme, with exception of its most posterior portion which remains as the bucconasal membrane
持続性鼻びれ
failure of the nasal fins to rupture during development leading to choanal obstruction/atresia
口鼻膜の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the thin, transient epithelial sheet which separates the primordial nasal cavity from the stomatodeum; in mammals, bucconasal membranes demarcate the locations of the paired primitive choanae

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.value: after lip fusion, degradation of the nasal fin and bucconasal membrane is necessary for reestablishing contact between the neonatal oral and nasal cavities through an open choana and for enabling nasal breathing in neonates

value.value: 口鼻膜の遺残
failure of the oronasal membrane to rupture during development leading to choanal obstruction
頬骨筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the zygomaticus major and/or minor facial muscles that originate from the body of the zygoma and pass downwards to insert into the corner of the mouth and lateral aspect of the upper lip, respectively; these muscles receive their nerve supply on their deep surface from the zygomatic and buccal branches of the facial nerve and lift the corners of the mouth
小頬骨筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the slender band of muscle on each side of the face that arises from the zygomatic bone, inserts into the upper lip between the zygomaticus major and the levator labii superioris, and acts to raise the upper lip upward and laterally
大頬骨筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the slender band of muscle on each side of the face that arises from the zygomatic bone, inserts into the orbicularis oris and skin at the corner of the mouth, and acts to pull the corner of the mouth upward and backward when smiling or laughing
鼓室上陥凹の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the upper portion of the tympanic cavity located above the tympanic membrane; it contains the head of the malleus and the body of the incus
丸く湾曲した鼻
appearance of the anterior facial part of the face or muzzle containing the oral and nasal regions is more circular than usual
広い鼻
increased width of the anterior facial part of the face or muzzle containing the oral and nasal regions
小さい鼻
decreased size of the anterior facial part of the face or muzzle containing the oral and nasal regions
狭い鼻
decreased width of the anterior facial part of the face or muzzle containing the oral and nasal regions
垂れ下がった鼻
muzzle has a curve or tilt such that the tip points downwards
短い人中
decreased length of the vertical groove found on the median line of the upper lip
上顎間縫合の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the anterior median suture between the two maxillae of the upper jawbone, located between the inferior border of the nasal aperture and the central incisor teeth; it usually ossifies later in life and becomes a synostosis
鼻骨間縫合の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cranial suture found between the left and right nasal bones
鼻骨上顎縫合の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cranial suture found between the nasal bone and the frontal process of the maxilla
鼻中隔の矮小化
reduced size of the dividing wall that runs down the midline of the nose, separating the nasal cavity into the two nostrils
鼻中隔の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the nasal septum, typically resulting in decreased size
鼻中隔の偏位

displacement of the nasal septum in which the top of the cartilaginous ridge leans to the left or the right, causing obstruction of the affected nasal passage; normally, the septum lies centrally, and thus the nasal passages are symmetrical
鼻中隔軟骨の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the hyaline cartilage of the nasal septum that is somewhat quadrilateral in shape, thicker at its margins than at its center, and completes the separation between the nasal cavities
鼻中隔軟骨の欠如
absence of the hyaline cartilage of the nasal septum that is somewhat quadrilateral in shape, thicker at its margins than at its center, and completes the separation between the nasal cavities
鼻中隔軟骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the nasal septum cartilage, typically resulting in decreased size
短い鼻中隔
reduced length of the dividing wall that runs down the midline of the nose, separating the nasal cavity into the two nostrils
